Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

WHAT WAS BROKEN:
- requireAuth() was hardcoded to bypass auth and inject 'demo-user' on every request
- clearCookie() didn't mirror setCookie() attributes, so logout couldn't clear cross-origin cookies
- Login button URL had no fallback for missing NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL
- OAuth callback swallowed Google's error responses (access_denied, etc.)
- SETUP.md referenced GEMINI_API_KEY but config.ts validates ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
- 'demo-user' workarounds were scattered across 5 service/route files

CHANGES (9 files):
- packages/backend/src/auth/session.ts: restore real requireAuth, fix clearCookie
- packages/backend/src/routes/auth.ts: handle Google error param, add diagnostic logging
- packages/backend/src/index.ts: log redirect URI + client ID at startup
- packages/backend/src/services/contracts.ts: remove all demo-user branching (4 places)
- packages/backend/src/routes/contracts.ts: reject contracts without Drive file
- packages/backend/src/routes/upload.ts: remove demo-user fallbacks, add 401 checks
- packages/backend/src/services/importDetect.ts: remove demo-user string check
- packages/web/app/page.tsx: add URL fallback to login button
- docs/SETUP.md: fix GEMINI_API_KEY -> ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST (Railway backend + Vercel frontend):
- Railway: GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI must exactly match Google Cloud Console
- Railway: WEB_ORIGIN must be the Vercel frontend URL
- Railway: NODE_ENV=production (enables Secure + SameSite=None cookies)
- Vercel: NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL must be the Railway backend URL
- Google Cloud Console: add both URLs to Authorized Origins + Redirect URIs
- Google Cloud Console: add test user emails under OAuth consent screen
